:R-HSA-162791  a            owl:NamedIndividual , obo:GO_0016255 ;
        rdfs:comment        "The mature form of urokinase plasminogen activator receptor (uPAR) is attached to the plasma membrane by a glycosylphosphatidylinositol (GPI) anchor (Ploug et al. 1991). As nascent uPAR polypeptide moves into the lumen of the endoplasmic reticulum, it is attacked by a transamidase complex that cleaves the uPAR polypeptide after residue 305, releasing the carboxyterminal peptide of uPAR and replacing it with an acylated GPI moiety. In a second step, the GPI moiety is deacylated, yielding a uPAR-GPI conjugate that can be efficiently transported to the Golgi apparatus." ;
        rdfs:label          "Attachment of GPI anchor to uPAR" ;
        dc:contributor      "GOC:reactome_curators" , "Authored: D'Eustachio, P, 2005-04-04 21:01:34" , "Edited: D'Eustachio, P, 0000-00-00 00:00:00" ;
        dc:date             "2026-06-29" ;
        pav:providedBy      "https://reactome.org" ;
        oboInOwl:hasDbXref  "R-HSA-162791" ;
        skos:narrower       <http://model.geneontology.org/R-HSA-163125/R-HSA-163125> ;
        skos:note           "org.biopax.paxtools.model.level3.Pathway" .

